.SH NAME
Selection.addRange \- Selection: addRange() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Selection.addRange()\f[B]\f[R] method adds a
\f[CR]Range\f[R] to a \f[CR]Selection\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
addRange(range)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]range\f[R]
A \f[CR]Range\f[R] object that will be added to the
\f[CR]Selection\f[R].
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Currently only Firefox supports multiple selection
ranges, other browsers will not add new ranges to the selection if it
already contains one.
.RE
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<p>
  I <strong>insist</strong> that you <strong>try</strong> selecting the
  <strong>strong words</strong>.
</p>
<button>Select strong words</button>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
let button = document.querySelector(\[dq]button\[dq]);

button.addEventListener(\[dq]click\[dq], () => {
  const selection = window.getSelection();
  const strongs = document.getElementsByTagName(\[dq]strong\[dq]);

  if (selection.rangeCount > 0) {
    selection.removeAllRanges();
  }

  for (const node of strongs) {
    const range = document.createRange();
    range.selectNode(node);
    selection.addRange(range);
  }
});
.EE
